[804.022582, "o", "GREP(1)            User Commands            GREP(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       grep, egrep, fgrep, rgrep - print lines that\u001b[m\r\n       match patterns\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mgrep\u001b[0m [\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m...] \u001b[4mPATTERNS\u001b[24m [\u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...]\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mgrep\u001b[0m [\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m...] \u001b[1m-e\u001b[0m \u001b[4mPATTERNS\u001b[24m ... [\u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...]\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mgrep\u001b[0m   [\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m...]   \u001b[1m-f\u001b[0m   \u001b[4mPATTERN_FILE\u001b[24m   ...\u001b[m\r\n       [\u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mgrep\u001b[0m  searches  for  \u001b[4mPATTERNS\u001b[24m  in each \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m.\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[4mPATTERNS\u001b[24m is one or more  patterns  separated\u001b[m\r\n       by  newline characters, and \u001b[1mgrep\u001b[0m prints each\u001b[m\r\n       line  that  matches  a  pattern.   Typically\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7mpage grep(1) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[805.470259, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[805.470365, "o", "       \u001b[4mPATTERNS\u001b[24m  should be quoted when \u001b[1mgrep\u001b[0m is used\u001b[m\r\n       in a shell command.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       A \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m of “\u001b[1m-\u001b[0m” stands for standard input.  If\u001b[m\r\n       no \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m is given, recursive searches examine\u001b[m\r\n       the  working  directory,  and   nonrecursive\u001b[m\r\n       searches read standard input.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Debian  also  includes  the variant programs\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1megrep\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mfgrep\u001b[0m and \u001b[1mrgrep\u001b[0m.  These programs  are\u001b[m\r\n       the  same  as \u001b[1mgrep\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-E\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mgrep\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-F\u001b[0m, and \u001b[1mgrep\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-r\u001b[0m,\u001b[m\r\n       respectively.  These variants are deprecated\u001b[m\r\n       upstream,  but  Debian provides for backward\u001b[m\r\n       compatibility. For portability  reasons,  it\u001b[m\r\n       is   recommended   to   avoid   the  variant\u001b[m\r\n       programs, and  use  \u001b[1mgrep\u001b[0m  with  the  related\u001b[m\r\n       option instead.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7mage grep(1) line 18 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[806.21953, "o", "\r\u001b[K/"]
[806.812262, "o", "\u001b[K-\b-"]
